      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: suppress acknowledgement-only replies",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nTelegram/forum turns could still emit low-value holding acknowledgements such as “Still working — I’ll update here” or final promise-only replies like “I’ll post the result in …”. Those messages looked like progress but closed or occupied the visible reply path without delivering the requested result.\n\nStale or route-only topic labels could also bias the model into promising delivery in a named topic instead of simply answering in the current chat.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Remove the automatic long-turn generic progress acknowledgement timer from reply dispatch.\n- Detect short promise-only final replies and mark the turn failed instead of treating the acknowledgement as a completed result.\n- Add prompt-level guidance that holding acknowledgements are not valid final answers.\n- Clarify that channel/topic/conversation labels are routing context only and must not be used as promised destinations.\n\n## Test\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.promise-only-ack.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/inbound-meta.test.ts src/agents/prompt-composition.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.promise-only-ack.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/inbound-meta.ts src/agents/system-prompt.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n",
